Russia eases rules for T - bill primary dealers . The Russian Central Bank will increase short cash position limits for primary dealers of Treasury Bills to two trillion roubles from 1 . 1 trillion roubles from March 24 , a spokesman said on Friday . The new terms will allow dealers to run up higher cash positions and increase liquidity of the T - bill market . All T - bills with a remaining security of 14 days or over will now be eligible for repos . Previously the maturity had been 1 - 3 months . Repos were started in October , allowing banks to run up a two - day overdraft with the Central Bank when buying government securities . - - Moscow Newsroom , + 7095 941 8520 
